The paper presents a new model-free algorithm for controlling linear quadratic (LQ) systems, which is a problem in control theory. The algorithm is based on a reduction of control of Markov decision processes to an expert prediction problem, which suggests a connection to machine learning and reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
